# Test Coverage

Every change to production code (`src/main/java`) must include or update tests in the same module.

## By change type

| Change type | Coverage expectation |
|-------------|---------------------|
| New Stream Language feature | Happy path + edge cases + invalid input |
| Bug fix | Regression test reproducing the bug |
| Refactor | Existing tests stay green; add tests if gaps exposed |
| Public API / SDK surface | Contract tests; parity with equivalent DSL where applicable |
| Operator reconciliation | Unit tests for diff logic; integration test for full reconcile loop |

## By deployment layer

| Layer | What to cover |
|-------|--------------|
| **Code** (`maestro-parser`) | Grammar rules, stages, predicates; assert on `StreamModel` records |
| **API** (`maestro-api`) | Builder output equals parser output for same topology |
| **Application** (`maestro-engine`, …) | Topology wiring, serde, config, lifecycle (start/stop/state) |
| **Operator** (`maestro-operator`, …) | Spec → model mapping, reconcile actions, status updates |

## What not to count as coverage

- Generated ANTLR lexer/parser — test through `StreamTopologyParser`
- Trivial record accessors — behavior tests suffice
- Logging-only changes — no test unless behavior changed
- Thin Docker/K8s manifests — validate via operator or integration tests, not manifest unit tests

## Verification

```bash
mvn verify                                    # all modules
mvn -pl maestro-parser test                   # code layer
mvn -pl maestro-engine test                   # application layer
```

Do not merge production changes with failing or missing tests for the changed behavior.
